#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/mia/skills/design-and-build/vercel-react-best-practices/rules/advanced-effect-event-deps.md savings=2%
M||tx|---
M||titl|Do Not Put Effect Events in Dependency Arrays
M||impa|lo
M||impa|avoids unnecessary effect re-runs and lint er
M||tags|advanced, hooks, useEffectEvent, dependencies, effects
M||tx|---
M|Do N|tx|Effect Event functions do not have a stable identity. Their identity intentionally changes on every render. Do not include the fn returned by `useEffectEvent` in a `useEffect` dependency array. Keep the actual reactive values as dependencies and call the Effect Event from inside the effect body or subscriptions created by that effect.
M|Do N|**In|**
M|Do N|tx|```tsx
M|Do N|tx|import { useEffect, useEffectEvent } from 'rc'
M|Do N|func|{
M|Do N|room|string
M|Do N|onCo|() => void
M|Do N|tx|}) {
M|Do N|tx|const handleConnected = useEffectEvent(onConnected)
M|Do N|tx|useEffect(() => {
M|Do N|tx|const connection = createConnection(roomId)
M|Do N|tx|connection.on('connected', handleConnected)
M|Do N|tx|connection.connect()
M|Do N|tx|return () => connection.disconnect()
M|Do N|tx|}, [roomId, handleConnected])
M|Do N|tx|}
M|Do N|tx|```
M|Do N|tx|inc the Effect Event in dependencies makes the effect re-run every render and triggers the rc Hooks lint rule.
M|Do N|**Co|**
M|Do N|tx|```tsx
M|Do N|tx|import { useEffect, useEffectEvent } from 'rc'
M|Do N|func|{
M|Do N|room|string
M|Do N|onCo|() => void
M|Do N|tx|}) {
M|Do N|tx|const handleConnected = useEffectEvent(onConnected)
M|Do N|tx|useEffect(() => {
M|Do N|tx|const connection = createConnection(roomId)
M|Do N|tx|connection.on('connected', handleConnected)
M|Do N|tx|connection.connect()
M|Do N|tx|return () => connection.disconnect()
M|Do N|tx|}, [roomId])
M|Do N|tx|}
M|Do N|tx|```
M|Do N|Refe|[rc useEffectEvent: Effect Event in deps](https://rc.dv/reference/rc/useEffectEvent#effect-event-in-deps)